                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Removing the damage table won't be done, imho. The nerf was way past due, its effective, and it leaves charm as a viable but not overpowered group dps tool. Soloing on my chanter is still significantly faster than soloing on my druid, so were still not as bad off as other classes, and we can still solo summoners, which most cant do.
<br />

<br />
Making all mobs dual wield naturally is crazy, mobs already double/triple plus bash or kick way too often, with near guaranteed quads clerics would need to med every other fight, and lower geared tanks would quit the game in despair.
<br />

<br />
100% sow with root & snare break on charm break is crazy imho. That would eliminate charm solo/duo for all but the best geared players, and do MORE damage to charm in group than the dps nerf imho. If your pet happens to eat you, root & snare classes would be helpless against your expet.
<br />

<br />
I personally would have preferred the 1% slow over the reduced damage tables, but I can see why sony didnt go that way. An unhasted mob isnt much of a threat, so it would skew the rvr in favor of the chanter. With the current solution, if you want the dps, you have to take the risk of hasting. Without haste on pet MOM, ER, doppleganger, stasis, and 3k of runes to begin with make survival trivial.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
