                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Im new to these boards, and thank their existance to help me grow and become a better player in the game.
<br />

<br />
I have to question both the developers and some of you who are able to hunt in zones I will only dream of while I play this game. I belong to a very small guild, which is powerful in its own right, but unable to hunt almost any of the GoD content, most of us are unflagged so most of the higher PoP content is locked to us as well. I say this to give an idea of where I can and cant hunt with my small groups.
<br />

<br />
I have played in LDoN and with 1 mob charmable in each instance ( havent found it yet - still looking )and DC taken away mezz hardly works, hmmmmm guess im not wanted or needed there.
<br />
Then with the nerf I have charmed mobs in OOW but cant get it to last more than 30 seconds! Mezz isnt necessary because the Druids and Rangers and such will just park the mobs because Mezz doesnt last long enough.
<br />

<br />
So what im getting at is this. Charm doesnt need to be reworked? I think your dead wrong. Without being in one of these super guilds how am I to compensate for the loss of the only viable way for me to add to a group besides be a buff bot? I find that DC has been A HUGE WASTE of AA points because unless im hunting in the basic planes its worthless. If I wanted to create this character to be merely a bot I would have dropped him to that status long ago. I like to play this character but I often regret makeing 65 as my abilities keep going away.
<br />

<br />
So the next question is - how do you moderate the power of the Enchanters in the upper guilds and power, yet make life bearable for those of us closer to the bottom? I honestly cant say. But takeing charm away essentially is not the way to do it.
<br />

<br />
Guess I just needed to give my 2cp worth
<br />

<br />
Azmezzu 65 Coercer</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
